ecdaa (0.9.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ David R. Bild ]
  * readme: add installation instructions and tighten some writing
  * readme: fix formatting
  * readme: add link to libsodium page
  * readme: add intro to installation section

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * An `apt-get` in the README should be `apt-key`
  * Our travis builds were using AMCL 4.7 but CMake/README used 4.6

  [ David R. Bild ]
  * cmake: add helper module to determine wordsize
  * cmake: use word_size when expanding templates
  * Do not hardcode BIG_256_66 for TPM
  * Do not hardcode BIG_256_56 for tests
  * Do not hardcode BIG_256_56 for examples

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * Make test vectors in BIG test chunk-size-dependent.
  * Move TPM-things into separate library, and only allow certain TPM curves
  * Print usable CMake error message if ECDAA_TPM_SUPPORT=ON but no TPM-allowed curve selected.
  * Use local copies of tpm-simulator scripts, and make a tpm-create-key utility
  * Use static allocation, not malloc, for TPM structs in tests.
  * Update the README
  * Use a user-provided source of randomness, not a user-space CSPRNG
  * Update README to explain new randomness.
  * Remove libsodium linking requirements.
  * Improve randomness tests in ecp-tests
  * Bump minor version number
  * Split debian packaging in two: libecdaa and libecdaa-tpm

 -- Zane Beckwith <zane.beckwith@xaptum.com>  Mon, 30 Apr 2018 20:43:46 +0000

